radiographic_examinations.findings: The liver enhances homogeneously without evidence of concerning focal lesion. There is no intrahepatic biliary ductal dilation. The portal vein is patent. Mild focal fatty infiltration is seen near the falciform ligament. The gallbladder is unremarkable. The pancreas enhances homogeneously without peripancreatic stranding or ductal dilation. The spleen shows no splenomegaly or focal lesion. The adrenal glands are normal. The kidneys enhance normally without hydronephrosis. The stomach and duodenum are unremarkable with normal non-dilated small bowel loops. There is a tubular structure arising from the cecum measuring up to 11-12 mm, with suspicion of acute appendicitis indicated by fluid and mucosal hyperenhancement. No mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy; the bladder and terminal ureters are normal. An IUD is appropriately positioned. The right ovary appears normal, but mild fluid is noted surrounding the inflamed appendix.
